<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 12:40:50 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>百岁老人的长寿免疫系统</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-long-lived-immune-system-of-centenarians</link><description>活到高龄的人的免疫系统有何独特之处？作者在这里描述了百岁老人可能通过多种机制实现如此长寿，包括限制炎症和免疫衰老的病理影响、保留免疫监视、持续肠道微生物多样性和维持肠道屏障完整性。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-long-lived-immune-system-of-centenarians.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 12:40:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-long-lived-immune-system-of-centenarians</guid></item><item><title>“最终，它成为了你”：新型“活体”膝关节置换术的发明者描述了为什么迫切需要这项技术及其工作原理</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/eventually-it-becomes-you-inventors-of-new-living-knee-replacement-describe-why-this-tech-is-desperately-needed-and-how-it-works</link><description>Live Science 与活体膝关节植入物的开发人员进行了交谈，该植入物可以帮助更多需要膝关节置换的患者获得膝关节置换术。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/eventually-it-becomes-you-inventors-of-new-living-knee-replacement-describe-why-this-tech-is-desperately-needed-and-how-it-works.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 12:25:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/eventually-it-becomes-you-inventors-of-new-living-knee-replacement-describe-why-this-tech-is-desperately-needed-and-how-it-works</guid></item><item><title>研究发现 DNA 可以以我们从未见过的方式构建</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/dna-can-be-built-in-a-way-weve-never-seen-before-study-finds</link><description>科学家们刚刚发现了一种全新的 DNA 合成方法。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dna-can-be-built-in-a-way-weve-never-seen-before-study-finds2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 12:10:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/dna-can-be-built-in-a-way-weve-never-seen-before-study-finds</guid></item><item><title>24,000年前的冰冻“僵尸蠕虫”被科学家解冻——然后它令人震惊地开始繁殖</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/24000-year-old-frozen-zombie-worm-thawed-by-scientists-then-it-shockingly-started-reproducing</link><description>它解冻了——然后它开始繁殖。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/24000-year-old-frozen-zombie-worm-thawed-by-scientists-then-it-shockingly-started-reproducing.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 11:55:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/24000-year-old-frozen-zombie-worm-thawed-by-scientists-then-it-shockingly-started-reproducing</guid></item><item><title>光离子钟中本征时间的量子特征</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/quantum-signatures-of-proper-time-in-optical-ion-clocks</link><description>一篇新的理论论文表明，俘获离子光学钟可以直接探测量子力学和广义相对论交叉点的微妙效应，包括固有时间的叠加和时间膨胀引起的纠缠。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quantum-signatures-of-proper-time-in-optical-ion-clocks2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 11:40:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/quantum-signatures-of-proper-time-in-optical-ion-clocks</guid></item><item><title>Bimekizumab 治疗斑块状银屑病的三年患者报告结果：开放标签扩展的 BE RADIANT 随机临床试验</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/three-year-patient-reported-outcomes-from-bimekizumab-for-plaque-psoriasis-the-be-radiant-randomized-clinical-trial-with-open-label-extension</link><description>在一项开放标签扩展的 3b 期随机临床试验中，bimekizumab 证明对中度至重度斑块型银屑病个体的患者报告结果和临床测量有快速和持续的改善。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/three-year-patient-reported-outcomes-from-bimekizumab-for-plaque-psoriasis-the-be-radiant-randomized-clinical-trial-with-open-label-extension.png" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 11:25:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/three-year-patient-reported-outcomes-from-bimekizumab-for-plaque-psoriasis-the-be-radiant-randomized-clinical-trial-with-open-label-extension</guid></item><item><title>约束理论在放射学中的应用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/application-of-the-theory-of-constraints-to-radiology</link><description>放射学吞吐量并不在于做得更多，而在于做得更多。这是为了解决瓶颈。将约束理论应用于成像工作流程，以识别真正的速率限制因素，并在资源紧张的环境中实现高影响力的流程改进。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/application-of-the-theory-of-constraints-to-radiology2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 11:10:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/application-of-the-theory-of-constraints-to-radiology</guid></item><item><title>基于深度学习的多动脉期 MRI 在肝细胞癌中的临床应用</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/clinical-utility-of-deep-learning-based-multiple-arterial-phase-mri-in-hepatocellular-carcinoma</link><description>肝细胞癌 (HCC) 诊断在很大程度上依赖于定时良好的动脉期 MRI，但单动脉期扫描常常会错过最佳的晚期动脉期，尤其是使用容易出现运动伪影和狭窄时序窗口的肝胆造影剂。这些限制可能会影响图像质量并减少对动脉期过度增强等关键特征的检测。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/clinical-utility-of-deep-learning-based-multiple-arterial-phase-mri-in-hepatocellular-carcinoma3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 10:55:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/clinical-utility-of-deep-learning-based-multiple-arterial-phase-mri-in-hepatocellular-carcinoma</guid></item><item><title>微流体装置比标准方法更快、更可靠地追踪细胞“柔软度”</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/microfluidic-device-tracks-cell-squishiness-faster-and-more-reliably-than-standard-methods</link><description>布朗大学的研究人员及其合作者开发了一种测量细胞特性的新方法，他们说这是一项重要的发展，因为准确测量细胞弹性的变化可以用来更好地了解疾病、诊断患者症状并提供更准确的预后。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/microfluidic-device-tracks-cell-squishiness-faster-and-more-reliably-than-standard-methods.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 10:40:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/microfluidic-device-tracks-cell-squishiness-faster-and-more-reliably-than-standard-methods</guid></item><item><title>DNA 修复衰老</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-dna-fix-for-aging</link><description>每个人的DNA都在不断变异。纠正这些错误可以延长寿命吗？&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-dna-fix-for-aging.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 10:25:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-dna-fix-for-aging</guid></item></channel></rss>